org.fujion.plotly.plot

Class PlotBar

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fujion.ancillary.Options
      • org.fujion.plotly.plot.PlotOptions
        • org.fujion.plotly.plot.PlotBar
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OptionMap.IOptionMapConverter, IClientTransform

    public class PlotBar
extends PlotOptions
    Options for bar plot.

    A bar plot presents categorical data with rectangular bars with heights or lengths proportional to the values that they represent. The bars can be plotted vertically or horizontally.

    • Field Detail

      • base

        @Option
public String base
        Determines where the bar base is drawn (in position axis units). In "stack" or "relative" bar mode, traces that set "base" will be excluded and drawn in "overlay" mode instead.

      • constraintext

        @Option
public PlotBar.ConstrainTextEnum constraintext
        Constrain the size of text inside or outside a bar to be no larger than the bar itself.

        Default: BOTH

      • dx

        @Option
public Double dx
        The x coordinate step. See x0 for more info.

      • dy

        @Option
public Double dy
        The y coordinate step. See y0 for more info.

public final ErrorBarOptions error_y
        Options for y-axis error bars.

      • hovertext

        @Option
public String hovertext
        Hover text elements associated with each (x,y) pair. If a single string, the same string appears over all the data points. If an array of string, the items are mapped in order to the this trace's (x,y) coordinates. To be seen, trace "hoverinfo" must contain a "text" flag.

        @Option(value="offset")
public int[] offset$array
        Shifts the position where the bar is drawn (in position axis units). In "group" bar mode, traces that set "offset" will be excluded and drawn in "overlay" mode instead.

      • offset$number

        @Option(value="offset")
public Integer offset$number
        Alternate form where offset is constant. Shifts the position where the bar is drawn (in position axis units). In "group" bar mode, traces that set "offset" will be excluded and drawn in "overlay" mode instead.

      • text$array

        @Option(value="text")
public String[] text$array
        Text elements associated with each (x,y) pair. The items are mapped in order to the this trace's (x,y) coordinates. If trace "hoverinfo" contains a "text" flag and "hovertext" is not set, these elements will be seen in the hover labels.

      • text$string

        @Option(value="text")
public String text$string
        Text elements associated with each (x,y) pair. Alternate form where the same string appears over all the data points. If trace "hoverinfo" contains a "text" flag and "hovertext" is not set, these elements will be seen in the hover labels.
